        "about.text": "New line is an innovative way to read long texts in the digital world, using gaze tracking technology. It's a glimpse into how we may read in the future - if we will still be able to do so.\n\nThe goal of the New Line project is to explore how we can use technology to enhance our reading experience in this age of distractions. Can we use the same tools that often pull us away from our focus and attention, to help us to be fully engaged even with something as simple as text?\n\nThis project was crafted by designer <a href=\"https://www.eladmedan.design\">Elad Medan</a>. It draws on insights from neurological research on eye behavior, the evolution of writing and printing, as well as cutting-edge technologies like eye tracking, parametric fonts, and the endless capabilities of computer screens. It aims to take advantage of the potential that modern technology can offer in the context of reading and typography.\n\nYou can read of the research behind New Line <a href=\"https://www.eladmedan.design/projects-en/usersreaders\">here</a>.\n\nIf you were inspired by this project or have any ideas for how it can be developed further, I'd love to <a href=\"http://mailto:new.line.reading@gmail.com\">hear from you!</a>\n\nThis project was created as part of the <a href=\"https://www.bezalel.ac.il/department/ma/visual_communication/program\">Visual Communication masters program</a> in Bezalel Academy, Jerusalem.\n\nThis website was developed by <a href=\"https://hafonton.co.il/\">Hafonton</a> and it uses <a href=\"https://gazerecorder.com/gazecloudapi/\">gazecloud</a> for eye-tracking.\n\nFonts in use -\nHebrew | Narkiss Text & Narkiss Block, courtesy of <a href=\"https://narkiss.fontef.com\">Fontef - Type Foundry</a>.\nLatin | Roboto Serif, from <a href=\"https://fonts.google.com\">Google Fonts</a>.\n\nTexts -\nHouse \n<a href=\"https://en.davar1.co.il/355419/\">Spider-Man is Jewish</a> by Barak Sella\n<a href=\"https://shortstoryproject.com/stories/house-taken-over/\">House Taken Over</a> by Julio Cortázar",
