        "help.title": "HELP",
        "help.head.1": "The Basics",
        "help.text.1": "Navigating text - looking in the reading direction moves forward, and looking against the reading direction moves backward.\nSkipping chapters -  to move forward a chapter keep your gaze towards the right edge of the screen, and to move back a chapter keep your gaze towards the left edge.\nSelecting chapters - keeping your gaze at the bottom of the screen displays the chapter bar. To navigate to a specific chapter, keep your gaze at its corresponding section.\nChanging the interface language - keep your gaze on the top left language icon.\nUsing the menu - keeping your gaze at the menu icon displays the top menu and pauses reading. To close the menu and resume reading, look at the X in the top right corner.",
        "help.head.2": "FAQ",
        "help.text.2": "### What do I do if I have authorized the browser to use the camera but can't get to the calibration screen?\nIf you have authorized the browser to use the camera but cannot access the calibration screen, check your privacy settings or the camera interface. If the issue persists, contact your network administrator as the camera may have additional protection from its software or operating system.\n\n### What do I do if the calibration process is stopped and does not allow me to continue?\nIf the calibration process is stopped it may be due to the camera having difficulty recognizing your face. Try to adjust the lighting in the room or move to a different location with better lighting. If you wear glasses, try removing them and recalibrating. If the problem persists, try recalibrating in a closed room with controlled lighting.\n\n### What if the interface reacts to my gaze in an unexpected way?\nIf the interface is responding imprecisely to your gaze, check to ensure that no one is behind you and that your face is fully visible to the camera. Adjust the distance of the screen from your face and refresh the page, then recalibrate the system.\n\n### What if the interface responds irregularly - sometimes it does and sometimes it doesn't?\nIf the interface is responding irregularly, try to maintain a consistent position during reading, same as the position during the calibration process. Adjust the angle of the camera or the screen and if the problem persists, refresh the page and recalibrate the system.\n",
